# ============================================================================
#  seeds.txt — YOUR taste, as a list of papers you love.
# ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
#  Copy this file to "seeds.txt" (same folder) and replace the examples below
#  with your own papers. This list IS how the radar learns what to find for you:
#  it studies these papers and looks for new work that resembles them.
#
#  HOW TO FILL IT IN — three easy ways, mix freely:
#    1. One DOI per line, e.g.   10.1093/poq/nfae012
#    2. One paste-in citation per line (APA or otherwise) — the radar will look
#       up its DOI for you.
#    3. Best of all: connect a Zotero library (see zotero.json.example and the
#       SETUP_GUIDE) so your seeds stay in sync with a folder you already curate.
#
#  Lines starting with "#" are comments and are ignored, so you can annotate.
#  Aim for at least ~15-20 papers to start; more is better. Add or remove any
#  time, then re-run:  python3 harvest.py --build-profile
#
#  The example DOIs below are real papers — DELETE them and add your own.
# ============================================================================

10.1093/poq/nfad063
10.1177/00936502231176435
10.1080/10584609.2023.2277956
10.1038/s41562-023-01587-9
